---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Welcome to Rewyr</h1>
			<p>
				Rewyr is a powerful CLI tool for <strong>rewiring</strong> your LLM-integrated applications. 
				It goes beyond static analysis by not only identifying LLM usage patterns in your codebase 
				but also intelligently improving them through its rewiring capabilities.
			</p>
			<p>
				Rewyr analyzes your LLM interactions, provides detailed insights, and suggests optimizations 
				to enhance performance, reduce costs, and improve reliability. Whether you're working with 
				OpenAI, Anthropic, or other LLM providers, Rewyr helps you optimize your AI workflows.
			</p>
			<h2>Key Features</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Atom Detection:</strong> Automatically detects LLM interaction points in your code</li>
				<li><strong>Template Extraction:</strong> Extracts and analyzes prompt templates</li>
				<li><strong>Metadata Analysis:</strong> Understands the context and purpose of each LLM call</li>
				<li><strong>RewireAgents:</strong> Intelligent agents that suggest specific improvements</li>
				<li><strong>Data Management:</strong> Collect and organize training examples for fine-tuning</li>
				<li><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong> Reduce costs and improve response quality</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>Core Concepts</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Atoms:</strong> Individual LLM interaction points that can be analyzed and optimized</li>
				<li><strong>RewireAgents:</strong> Specialized improvement agents for different optimization strategies</li>
				<li><strong>Templates:</strong> Extracted prompt patterns for better understanding and optimization</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Get started by installing Rewyr and running <code>wyr init</code> on your project to begin 
				analyzing your LLM usage patterns. Check out our <a href="/blog">blog</a> for insights, 
				tutorials, and updates on the latest features.
			</p>
			<p>
				Ready to optimize your AI workflows? 
				<a href="https://github.com/rewyr/rewyr" target="_blank">Visit our GitHub repository</a> 
				to learn more and contribute to the project.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
